channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Report: Biden Expected to Meet With Family at Camp David to Discuss the Future of His Campaign
Nikki Haley says GOP should prepare for 'younger,' more 'vibrant' Biden replacement
item.description: Haley warned Republicans that Democrats will likely replace President Biden on the ticket with someone younger and more vibrant following his debate performance.

item.title: GOP Recruits Poll Monitors for Dem-Leaning Cities
item.description: The Republican National Committee (RNC) is recruiting suburbanites to monitor the polls in largely Democrat-leaning cities for Election Day.

item.title: Hilarious: Adam Kinzinger Endorsed Joe Biden, Then Came the Debate. Now, Watch Him Scramble.
Jill Biden's ex-husband calls her out for defending 'struggling' Joe Biden, 'keeping him in the race'
item.description: Jill Biden's ex-husband recently told the New York Post he was surprised the first lady is "adamant" about keeping President Biden in the race after Thursday's debate.

item.title: Big-Money Donors 'Disappointed' but Sticking With Biden
item.description: Many wealthy donors will continue to finance President Joe Biden's campaign despite his inane debate performance, the New York Post reports.

item.title: HOT TAKES: Biden Apologists Have Come Up With the Wildest Excuse Yet for Debate Loss—It's CNN's Fault
Atlanta Journal-Constitution editorial board calls for Biden to drop out 'for the good of the nation'
item.description: The Atlanta Journal-Constitution called for President Biden to bow out of the presidential election "for the good" of the U.S. after his disastrous debate performance.

item.title: Trump: Biden 'Choked,' Was in a 'Trance' During Debate
item.description: President Joe Biden "choked" during their CNN debate and appeared to be in a "trance," former President Donald Trump wrote Saturday on Truth Social.

item.title: Freefall: Major Swing State Newspaper Tells Biden to 'Pass the Torch' After Debate Fiasco
The Democrats' social media account attempts to spin Biden's debate debacle: 'Did we watch the same debate?'
item.description: The Democrats' social media account got roasted in the comment section after its claime President Biden won the presidential debate against former president Trump.

item.title: Carville: 'Weird' to See Name Being Used in Biden Fundraising
item.description: Political strategist James Carville, whose name was used in Biden fundraising messages Saturday after he predicted the president wouldn't be on the ballot this November.

item.title: The People of California Will Finally Be Heard on the Fate of Prop. 47, Despite Efforts to Thwart Them
European official appears to liken Biden to failed Roman emperor after disastrous debate performance
item.description: Polish Foreign Minister Radosław Sikorski seemed to reference President Biden's poor debate performance to the Roman emperor Commodus in a social media post this week.

item.title: Ben Carson to Newsmax: Threat of 25th Amendment May Convince Biden
item.description: It may take the threat of invoking the 25th Amendment to convince President Joe Biden to step aside following his uneven debate performance Thursday with former President Donald Trump, former Department of Human Services Secretary Ben Carson said on Newsmax Saturday.
